        <h2>Fuller's earth (multani mitti)</h2>
        <div class="xyz">
            <div class="pqr">
        <p>We Indians just love multani mitti for our skin, don't we? Well, you can use it for your hair too, because multani mitti helps to strip away excess oil, thereby controlling the production of oil by the scalp.
             Further, it helps to increase blood circulation, which further promotes hair growth.</p>
        <p>How to use</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Soak the multani mitti in water for two to three hours, and make a thick paste out of it. </li>
            <li>Add tomato juice to multani mitti, and mix it properly.</li>
            <li>Apply it on the scalp, and leave it on for 20 minutes. After that, rinse it off with lukewarm water.</li>
        </ol>   
